<subSubSection id="02494D53992AB0DC040B4158D2EEC6D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="13CC96C4624AD8A6EF19FC1DE48B01AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C71B3CE4C9E8772B4406F0CB1AD471C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.0-2.1 mm long (mean = 2.03 mm; n = 3); 2.5-2.86
<normalizedToken id="F9929F69660D8E5BA50495C7D567BE80" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the elytral disc shallowly transversely impressed with a saddle-like depression; elytral interstriae flat with moderate interstrial tubercles posterior to the saddle; and declivity steep, slightly flattened.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="63A72C370FF4C984F139936858DC2E99" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="5CCC1F0028F5F5D88568269C6EBC5103" baseAuthorityName="Sampson" baseAuthorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microperus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microperus undulatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undulatus">
<emphasis id="16499BB1FAA0442FFD084F7C8EE5E0C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Microperus undulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="F5C372E98FE4C2A591542F141B314F5C" genus="M." lsidName="M. sagmatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sagmatus">
<emphasis id="02A795490AD536FE67E8A79101D8D200" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. sagmatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is distinguished by the discal impression shallower, antero-posteriorly broader, with gentler anterior and posterior slopes, strial punctures on impression without granules, interstrial tubercles on disc behind saddle moderately sized with rounded apices pointing dorsally, not backwardly hooked.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
